Encrypt Stuff with openssl Bash Scripts
Produced by a citizen of the Nation of Flos Regium: https://flosregium.online
License: TNOFRS License (See License File)
Privacy Respecting Browser Startpage: https://historya.live/start/
=========================================

These bash scripts are designed to make it easy to encrypt/decrypt text and/or files using openssl.

How to use:
* Obtain the script package
* Read and agree to the short license
* Make the script(s) runable (chmod +x filename)
* The encrypt-file.sh does the thing
* The decrypt-file.sh does the thing but in reverse
* The encrypt-text.sh does the thing with text
* The encrypt-text.sh does the thing with text but reverse
